{"number":57452,"title":"[CodeGen] hierarchyBuilding decorator generates incorrect constructor base() calls in multi-level discriminated hierarchy","body":"## Bug Description

When using `@Azure.ClientGenerator.Core.Legacy.hierarchyBuilding` decorator on models in a **multi-level discriminated inheritance hierarchy**, the C# generator produces constructor `base()` calls with **wrong parameter ordering**, resulting in `CS1503` compilation errors.

## Context

This was discovered during the MPG migration of `Azure.ResourceManager.AlertsManagement` (tracking issue #56945).

## Swagger Model Hierarchy (Original)

The original Swagger defines a 3-level discriminated hierarchy via `allOf`:

```
AlertEnrichmentItem          (discriminator: &#34;type&#34;)
  └── PrometheusEnrichmentItem   (allOf → AlertEnrichmentItem, x-ms-discriminator-value: &#34;PrometheusEnrichmentItem&#34;)
        ├── PrometheusInstantQuery   (allOf → PrometheusEnrichmentItem, x-ms-discriminator-value: &#34;PrometheusInstantQuery&#34;)
        └── PrometheusRangeQuery     (allOf → PrometheusEnrichmentItem, x-ms-discriminator-value: &#34;PrometheusRangeQuery&#34;)
```

Source: `specification/alertsmanagement/resource-manager/Microsoft.AlertsManagement/AlertsManagement/preview/2025-05-25-preview/AlertsManagement.json`

## TypeSpec Spec Configuration

In `models.tsp`, `PrometheusInstantQuery` and `PrometheusRangeQuery` use `extends AlertEnrichmentItem` (skipping the intermediate `PrometheusEnrichmentItem`), then use `@hierarchyBuilding(PrometheusEnrichmentItem)` to re-insert the intermediate class:

```typespec
@discriminator(&#34;type&#34;)
model AlertEnrichmentItem {
  title: string;
  description: string;
  status: Status;
  errorMessage?: string;
  type: Type;
}

model PrometheusEnrichmentItem extends AlertEnrichmentItem {
  linkToApi: string;
  datasources: string[];
  grafanaExplorePath: string;
  query: string;
  type: Type.PrometheusEnrichmentItem;
}

@Azure.ClientGenerator.Core.Legacy.hierarchyBuilding(PrometheusEnrichmentItem)
model PrometheusInstantQuery extends AlertEnrichmentItem {
  ...PrometheusEnrichmentItemProperties;
  time: string;
  type: Type.PrometheusInstantQuery;
}

@Azure.ClientGenerator.Core.Legacy.hierarchyBuilding(PrometheusEnrichmentItem)
model PrometheusRangeQuery extends AlertEnrichmentItem {
  ...PrometheusEnrichmentItemProperties;
  start: utcDateTime;
  end: utcDateTime;
  step: string;
  type: Type.PrometheusRangeQuery;
}
```

## Generated C# Code (Incorrect)

The C# class hierarchy is **correct**:
```
AlertEnrichmentItem → PrometheusEnrichmentItem → PrometheusInstantQuery / PrometheusRangeQuery
```

But the **constructor `base()` calls are wrong**. In `PrometheusEnrichmentItem.cs`:

```csharp
// AlertEnrichmentItem constructor signature:
//   (string title, string description, AlertsManagementStatus status, Type @type)

// Constructor #1 — WRONG: discriminator value inserted as first arg, shifting all params
internal PrometheusEnrichmentItem(string title, string description, AlertsManagementStatus status, ...)
    : base(&#34;PrometheusEnrichmentItem&#34;, title, description, status)
//         ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^  ^^^^  ^^^^^^^^^^  ^^^^^^
//         → string title (OK)       → string description (OK)  → AlertsManagementStatus status (WRONG: expects AlertsManagementStatus)  → Type @type (WRONG: gets AlertsManagementStatus)

// Constructor #3 — WRONG: Type passed as first arg
private protected PrometheusEnrichmentItem(string title, ..., Type @type, ...)
    : base(@type, title, description, status)
//         ^^^^^
//         Type → string title (WRONG)
```

## Compilation Errors

```
CS1503: Argument 4: cannot convert from &#39;AlertsManagementStatus&#39; to &#39;Type&#39;
  → PrometheusEnrichmentItem.cs:25, PrometheusInstantQuery.cs:25, PrometheusRangeQuery.cs:27

CS1503: Argument 1: cannot convert from &#39;Type&#39; to &#39;string&#39;
  → PrometheusEnrichmentItem.cs:61
```

## Root Cause Analysis

The C# generator assumes the base class constructor follows a **discriminator-first** parameter pattern (where the discriminator value is the first positional argument). This works for simple 2-level hierarchies (as in the Spector test `hierarchy-building`), but fails when:

1. The discriminator property (`type`) is **not the first** parameter in the base class constructor — `AlertEnrichmentItem`&#39;s constructor has `(string title, string description, AlertsManagementStatus status, Type @type)` with discriminator at position 4.
2. The `@hierarchyBuilding` creates a **3-level** hierarchy where the intermediate class (`PrometheusEnrichmentItem`) inherits from the discriminator root (`AlertEnrichmentItem`).

The generator inserts the discriminator value string (e.g., `&#34;PrometheusEnrichmentItem&#34;`) or the `Type @type` parameter as the **first** argument in `base()`, causing all subsequent arguments to shift by one position and produce type mismatches.

## Expected Behavior

The generated `base()` calls should match the base class constructor&#39;s actual parameter positions:

```csharp
// Constructor #1 — should pass discriminator at the correct position (4th arg)
internal PrometheusEnrichmentItem(string title, string description, AlertsManagementStatus status, ...)
    : base(title, description, status, &#34;PrometheusEnrichmentItem&#34;)

// Constructor #3 — should pass Type at the correct position (4th arg)
private protected PrometheusEnrichmentItem(string title, ..., Type @type, ...)
    : base(title, description, status, @type)
```

## Reproduction

```powershell
cd sdk/alertsmanagement/Azure.ResourceManager.AlertsManagement
dotnet build /t:GenerateCode /p:LocalSpecRepo=&#34;/specification/alertsmanagement/resource-manager/Microsoft.AlertsManagement/AlertsManagement&#34;
dotnet build  # CS1503 errors
```

## Environment

- Generator: `@azure-typespec/http-client-csharp-mgmt@1.0.0-alpha.20260323.4`
- Package: `Azure.ResourceManager.AlertsManagement` v1.2.0-beta.1
